questions.question: Describe two political reasons and two economic reasons why World War II started.

model_answer.text: One political reason was the rise of fascist leaders like Hitler and Mussolini.
model_answer.category: economic reasons why World War II started

model_answer.text: Another political reason was the failure of the League of Nations to prevent aggression.
model_answer.category: economic reasons why World War II started

model_answer.text: A third political factor was the policy of appeasement by Britain and France, which allowed aggressive powers to expand unchecked.
model_answer.category: economic reasons why World War II started

model_answer.text: Additionally, the spread of nationalist ideologies created tensions among European countries.
One economic reason was the Great Depression, which caused massive unemployment and instability.
Another economic reason was Germany’s economic hardships due to the Treaty of Versailles reparations.
model_answer.category: economic reasons why World War II started

model_answer.text: A third economic factor was the global decline in trade and production, which fueled protectionism and economic rivalries.
Moreover, inflation and poverty in post-war Europe created conditions ripe for political extremism.

questions.question: Explain what the Blitz was and its effect on British civilians.

model_answer.text: The Blitz was a sustained bombing campaign by Nazi Germany against Britain, especially London, from 1940 to 1941.
Its effect on civilians included thousands of deaths, destruction of homes, fear, and the evacuation of children to the countryside.

questions.question: Describe one major battle in WWII.

model_answer.text: The Battle of Stalingrad was a turning point in the war; Soviet forces successfully defended the city against the German army, causing heavy German losses.
The Battle of Midway was a crucial naval battle where the US Navy defeated the Japanese fleet, shifting the balance of power in the Pacific.

questions.question: Describe how the Holocaust was carried out.

model_answer.text: The Holocaust was systematically carried out by the Nazis through ghettos, mass shootings, deportations, extermination camps like Auschwitz, gas chambers, and forced labor, resulting in the murder of millions of Jews and other minorities.

questions.question: Describe one reason why the United States joined World War II, and give two consequences of its involvement.

model_answer.text: One reason was the bombing of Pearl Harbor by Japan.
Two consequences were that the U.S. helped defeat the Axis powers and became a world superpower.
model_answer.category: reason why the United States joined World War II

model_answer.text: Additionally, its economy was boosted by wartime production.
